properties.abstract: Dent de Combette and Rochers des Rayes stand at the south-west end of the Gastlosen chain. It is a shame that in the southern part of Gastlosen there is no accommodation available.
properties.subtitle: Looking for accomodation

segments.description: From the Rougemont railway station follow the hiking route through the village to reach the La Forcla (1208 m) col. Descend to the bridge across La Manche (1122 m) and ascend to La Planche, either on the road or directly in pastures. Continue on roads and hiking trails via Raye du Baillif, Raye au Sex and Combette to reach the saddle at P. 1839.
segments.title: Rougemont – P. 1839

segments.description: Ascend to Selle Aubert (P. 1897 m, unnamed on the map). Continue on the increasingly steep SW face with small fir trees, until the rocks force you to turn left. Scramble up in a steep bowl to reach the SW ridge and the summit rocks. Climb 20 metres in a steep gully to reach the narrow Corne Aubert summit (2036 m). The descent back to P. 1839 is on the ascent.

segments.title: P. 1839 - Corne Aubert – P. 1839

segments.description: Follow the hiking trail to the rocky Doigt de Combette (P. 1941, unnamed on the map). The trail passes the summit on the north side, but those who have stamina can climb it. Continue on the marked path, initially on the left-hand side of the ridge line, then on the right-hand side to reach P. 1975. Here the steep trail to Dent de Combette (2082 m) marked blue-white branches off. Initially it is very steep, overcoming escarpments (fixed rope), then it turns right to a slightly exposed traverse (chains), and finally it turns left back to the ridge. Follow the ridge to the summit. Ca. 40 m before the summit a trail equipped with steel cables and marked by pale red arrows descends on the north-west side; T4.

segments.title: P. 1839 – Dent de Combette

segments.description: After this detour go back to the hiking trail leading up and down to Rochers des Rayes (2026 m), whose highest point is on the left-hand side. The descent is on the SW ridge via Montagne aux Manges until the hut on the ridge at P. 1519. Descend to La Manche and La Planche to reach the ascent route. Hike back to Rougemont via La Forcla.
segments.title: Dent de Combette – Rochers de Rayes – Rougemont

segments.description: Begin at Grubenberghütte SAC and hike to Le Savigny via the Amelier saddle. (From here a detour to Dent de Savigny is possible.) From the Amelier saddle ascend to the Selle Aubert (P. 1897 m, unnamed on the map) on a faint path; 2 h leaving out Dent de Savigny, 4 h including it.
segments.title: Variant 1: starting point Grubenberghütte SAC

segments.description: Begin at Cabane des Marindes CAS and follow a marked hiking trail via Le Sori and La Porsogne to P.1839 above Pertet à Bovets; ca. 2½ h.
segments.title: Variant 2: starting point Cabane des Marindes CAS
